# rustc-Quellcheckout: nur Referenzlektüre, keine Abhängigkeit (DESIGN.md §1.2)
/rustc-src

# Rust
/target/

# javac-/fastjavac-Ausgaben in den Beispielen: alles außer den Quellen
examples/*
!examples/*.java
# Vire-Beispielprogramme + Runner/README sind Quellcode, kein Build-Artefakt.
!examples/vire/

# kompilierte Stub-Klassenbibliothek
/stdlib/out/
benchmarks/m0/q[0-9]*

# Java-Bootstrap Build-Artefakte
examples/*.class
examples/*.bin
examples/bench
tests/work/

# Autonomer Arbeits-Journal (nicht committen)
workflow.md

# Vendored cuda-oxide (NVlabs, Apache-2.0): reference-only, `exclude`d from the
# workspace and NEVER compiled/linked (only the @gpu *design* was adapted — no
# code copied; see LICENSING.md / language/GPU-KERNELS.md). The bulky upstream
# source tree is untracked; refresh it locally with `sh crates/cuda-oxide/update.sh`.
# Kept tracked: the attribution note, its license text, and the pull script.
crates/cuda-oxide/*
!crates/cuda-oxide/NOTICE.md
!crates/cuda-oxide/LICENSE
!crates/cuda-oxide/update.sh
